projects.name: Shoebill
projects.description: Shoebill is a custom interpreter built in Go, implementing a C-like syntax with modern features. It supports variable bindings, integers, booleans, arithmetic expressions, built-in functions, and robust data structures like strings, arrays, and hashes.  Notably, Shoebill features first-class and higher-order functions, closures, and is parsed using a Pratt parsing technique. This project demonstrates my understanding of language design and implementation, from parsing to runtime environment.
